            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ublio</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Mari</abbr><ex>o</ex></expan> Mariani filio <lb n="2"/>Calpurniano Or<lb break="no" n="3"/><expan><abbr>ret</abbr><ex>ano</ex></expan> defuncto <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>norum</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost">X</supplied>VIII <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>Mari</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> Marianus <supplied reason="lost">co</supplied>mmuni <lb n="5"/>adfectione Mariae Calpurni<lb break="no" n="6"/>ae uxoris et matris recep<lb break="no" n="7"/>to in clientelam civium <lb n="8"/><expan><abbr>Aesonens</abbr><ex>ium</ex></expan> <lb n="9"/>et liberalibus <lb n="10"/>studiis erudito impetra<lb break="no" n="11"/>to loco ex <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecreto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>ord</abbr><ex>inis</ex></expan> <lb n="12"/>statua equestri memo<lb break="no" n="13"/>riam piaetatis <note>sic</note> hono<lb break="no" n="14"/>rav<expan><ex>i</ex><abbr>t</abbr></expan> datisque spor<lb break="no" n="15"/>tulis dedicavit
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>(B): CIL, IRC, AE 1988: geringfügig abweichende Textwiedergaben. Nach IRC einzige im Nordteil der iberischen Halbinsel bekannte Ehrung mit einer Reiterstatue.</p>
            </div>
